1. pip install pyinstaller
2. Add an Exclusion to Windows Defender
    If you are confident that your script is safe, you can add an exclusion in Windows Defender for your
    specific .exe file or the entire project directory. Here’s how to add an exclusion:
    2.1. Open Windows Security (you can search for it in the Start menu).
    2.2. Click on “Virus & threat protection.”
    2.3. Under "Virus & threat protection settings," select “Manage settings.”
    2.4. Scroll down to “Exclusions” and click on “Add or remove exclusions.”
    2.5. Click on “Add an exclusion,” choose “File” or “Folder,” and then select the .exe file or
    the folder containing it.
3. pyinstaller --onefile main.py "your entry point to your app"